    GEOPlatformSearch

    GEOPlatformSearch.Rd

    search for GEO platform name updated 02/2024

    GEOPlatformSearch(
  x,
  organism = NULL,
  file = GEOplatform,
  contain_all = TRUE,
  accession_only = FALSE
)

    Arguments

    x

    a string or character vector to search for. input character vector if searching for multiple terms.

    organism

    organism name to narrow down the search. partial input of an organism name is allowed. e.g. results for organism "Homo sapiens" will be pulled if input "homo".

    file

    GEO platform information dataframe. columns: "Accession", "Name", "Technology", "Organism".

    contain_all

    if TRUE, results contain all search terms will be returned. if FALSE, results contain any of the given term will be returned.

    accession_only

    if TRUE, only accession id of the search will be returned as a character. if FALSE, the complete information of the platforms will be returned as a dataframe.

    Value

    character or dataframe of search result

    Examples

    GEOPlatformSearch("illumina")
#>       Accession                                        Name
#> 3482   GPL30366        illumina novaseq 6000 (Mus musculus)
#> 3757   GPL30028        illumina NovaSeq 6000 (Mus musculus)
